# E.A.R.T.H. (Environmental Action & Response Through Human-AI Technology)

## ğŸŒ Overview
E.A.R.T.H. is an innovative platform designed to empower communities in taking action against environmental issues. By harnessing the power of AI and gamification, we provide a user-friendly space where individuals can report problems, share insights, and collaborate for a sustainable future.

## ğŸš€ Features
- *Interactive Map:* Easily pinpoint environmental issues and share updates in real-time.
- AI-Powered Insights : Automatically analyze uploaded images using the Gemini API to identify environmental problems.
- Community Engagement : Join discussions, follow other users, and collaborate on projects.
- Gamification :  Earn points, badges, and rewards for contributing to sustainability efforts.

## ğŸ›  Technologies Used
- Gemini API : For advanced image recognition and classification of environmental issues.
- Folium & OpenStreetMap : To create interactive maps that visualize user-reported data.
- Streamlit : For building an intuitive and responsive web interface.
- Supabase : For user authentication and real-time database management.
- Python : The backbone of our application, powering the logic and integration of all components.

## ğŸ“š How to Get Started
1. Clone the Repository :
   bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/EARTH.git
   cd EARTH
   
2. *Install Dependencies:*
   bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   
3. *Run the Application:*
   bash
   streamlit run app.py
   

